{
  "texts": [
    "It is unfortunate that some schools may prioritize sending students to prestigious universities rather than focusing on holistic development.",
    "To address this, your suggestion of cross-school teaching research and exchanges is excellent.",
    "By sharing quality education courses and results among schools in the same area, it can create a collaborative learning environment and promote the adoption of effective teaching practices.",
    "In addition, involving the Education Bureau in the assessment of these activities would provide further accountability and encourage schools to actively participate in the reform.",
    "By making it a part of the school assessment, it sends a clear message that quality education is valued and should be a priority."
  ]
}